Mutton Bamboo Briyani was very nice. The flavours were awesome and there was so much of mutton. Definitely one that I would highly recommend.
Great variety and reasonable prices. One that I would surely recommend.
Ordered a 2KG vegetarian cake for the office and it was a wonderful job done by Mrs. Yasho. Everyone loved it. The cake was so aromatic and delicious. A highly recommended home baker!
Their Shrimp Paste Chili is a tad too salty. So be cautious when taking this.
Pork Spring Rolls is another hot seller here. Each is about 6 inches long and is priced at RM 2. Tastes okay I would say.
Sweet Potato Leaves is pretty much what you get here for vegetable's. Tasty and reasonably priced.
Fried Tang Hoon is another house specialty. Very tasty and cheap.
Hokkien Mee is prepared using hand made Pan Mee. Very different taste wise and probably takes an acquired taste to appreciate it. Cheap though.
A lovely beach tucked in a Chinese Fishing Village. You could buy fresh seafood directly from the fishermen or visit some of those Chinese Restaurants that serve delicious food and very cheap prices
A lovely beach to chill or even do picnics. Amenities are great and the sunset views are awesome.
Rice and Curries weren't impressive. In fact, it was a let down for me.

Salt Baked Fish was tasty as well. As you can see, grilling is done using conventional methods.

tip.text: Sauteed Onions Chicken Hot Dog. The onions were nothing much, in fact it was bad. Bun was dry and not the best. The frankfurter however was heavenly. Simply excellent. For that, I'd recommend this.
Cheesy Mushroom Fries was not up to my expectations. He fries were horrible and there was no trail of cheese in that cheesy thingy. Mushrooms were okay though. I'd recommend skipping this.
Onion Rings were horrible. The onions were stale and could not eminate any flavours. The outer batter was horrible, coarse and bland too. Don't waste your money on this one.
Pulled Chicken Burger was a shame. Such a small portion and it was pathetic quality wise. Not one that I would recommend.
Lemonade was nice but not great. I wonder how this got to be famous. Prices are steep and do note that you get free flow for the drinks.
Do try their Hot Chocolate. It's real Magnum Chocolate that's melted down. Tastes heavenly!
Affogato was excellent. One that I would recommend.
Hokkien Mee is good but the noodles is slightly thicker and chewy. Also so Sambal Belacan. Otherwise a good one to try.
Fried Rice is excellent here. Perhaps the best that I have come across in Kajang.
Even the clear soup which was provided complimentary was very tasty. A must visit place when you're in Broga.
Dry Hakka Noodles is a signature dish here. The noodles was so good, comes with lots of minced pork and Char Siew and the blend of sauces was heavenly. Highly recommended.
The stall opens daily from 8.30 am till 4 pm. Located right opposite the police station.
Ais Kacang was excellent here. Old school style of preparation and comes with lots of ingredients. Highly recommended.
Teochew Spicy Grilled Fish was excellent. It was so good that we ended up scooping the broth when the fish was done. Highly recommended and it's so cheap.

formattedAddress: G-22, Jalan Taman Kajang Sentral 1, Taman Kajang Sentral

tip.text: Southwest Chicken comes with two huge cuts grilled to perfection and served with two sides of your choice. Juicy meat and totally worth it.
Grilled Lamb Shoulder is another must try here. Way cheaper that those big brands and is so worth it. Thick cut and delicious marination.
Mushroom Soup is really something. Made with lots of diced mushrooms and it's thick and concentrated. Highly recommend. Definitely not those off the can stuffs.
Masala Prawn Fry comes with lots of gravy and is mildly spicy. Decent amount of shrimps too.
Chettinad Mutton was decent. Dry gravy and comes with lots of bones. If you dislike bones, then his isn't for you.
Onion Pakkora was awesome. This comes from Simon Box Food and it's their top seller. A must try here.
Aloo Paratha was decent. Right size and good stuffing.
Punjabi Samosa's are the frozen ones that they fry on request. Mine came with the fillings being frozen and they replaced it with charred ones.
Mutton Briyani was good. Not the usual moist type and comes with lots of sides. Since the merger with Simple Box Food, their Briyani's have improved tremendously.
Pineapple Shake is another one that I would highly recommend here. Absolutely delicious and it's so refreshing.
Authentic Coconut Shakes made with real coconut juice. Unlike the famous Klebang one, this is not blended with Ice Cream but topped with it. Very authentic flavours. Must try.
Ikan Bakar and Ayam Bakar were good. Unfortunately no Ayam Percik available.
A few stalls selling a variety of Malay Cakes but overall, it was a quite disappointing experience. Less than 20 stalls as they have all migrated to Behrang 2020.
Karipap Sambal is one of the local delicacies in Tanjung Malim. A must try item at this bazaar.
The Murtabak was horrible. No taste of chicken and it was fully stuffed with eggs. Even that was tasteless. Not really recommended.
The Peanut Sauce is thicker, crunchier as it comes with lots of coarsely ground peanuts and is spicy. Perfect for the sweet satays.

venue.name: Char Kuey Teow & Pork Satay Tokong

tip.text: Their Pork Satay is another must try item here. Lean meat marinated in sweet sauce. Extremely tasty and only 90 Sen each.

venue.name: Char Kuey Teow & Pork Satay Tokong

tip.text: Opens 7 pm to 10 pm, Mondays to Thursday's. Come early as she sells out quite fast.

venue.name: Char Kuey Teow & Pork Satay Tokong

tip.text: The Auntie's Char Kuey Teow is very different and extremely tasty. She literally fries the Kuey Teow on N egg. Must try dish!

venue.name: Char Kuey Teow & Pork Satay Tokong

tip.text: Despite having been charged RM 16 for this meal, I still found it to be very reasonable. Fish was fried on request too. Mutton Varuval was good and the egg curry was awesome.
Do try Satay Awe stall here. In my opinion, they are the Top 5 Satay place in Kajang and a must try.
Lamb Zurbian was totally out of this world. Absolutely amazing dish. Rice, the slow cooked lamb and even the Chicken Kurma on the sides, simply heavenly! Highly recommended.
Chicken Parmesana was delicious. Huge portions too. But still their lamb was the best.
Even their Fajitas wraps were so tender and thin. I would strongly recommend giving their Fajitas a try.
Lamb Fajitas were awesome. Cooked with onions, carrots and some herbs, it tasted so close to Corned Mutton. Highly recommended!
Not only are their Half Baked Cheese Tarts good, even their buns and Mini Cheese Tarts were awesome. Soft, fluffy buns that comes with quality ingredients. Highly recommended!
Excellent Nasi Kandar variety for lunch and reasonable prices. Best time to go is for lunch. Food is good too.
Their Roasted Chicken was awesome. Seriously some good stuff but the noodles was bland and tasteless. Stick with their Chicken Rice and avoid this noodles please.

formattedAddress: No. 2 Block E, Jalan GC 4, Glomac Cyberjaya (Cyber 12)

tip.text: The food prices are very cheap but sadly they aren't as good as they should. Watered down curries and the food wasn't fresh.

tip.text: For RM 1.00 , the Satay is small and comes with 70% fat and 30% meat. Peanut dip is lighter too and a little too sweet. Not one that I would recommend.
Yatie's Nasi Lemak has more rice, less Sambal and is milder in spiciness and would suit those who can't palate spicy food. Though my vote shall be for Suri's, this too is a good packet of Nasi Lemak.
Moroccan Lamb Burger was very good as well. A variety of ingredients and loved he burst of flavours.
Soda Americano was an excellent brew. A good coffee with a twist.
Nuttella Cheese Cake is one that I would recommend. Loved the texture and rich in flavours.
Their Chili Paste was awesome! Must have with your Hokkien Mee.

tip.text: Hokkien Mee is very good but pricey. RM 9 for one person. Hardly any lard seen when you ask for extra lard. Nevertheless the taste is still good.

venue.name: Restoran Ahwa 新青山亚华福建面

tip.text: The cupcakes from Yasho's Home Baker was amazing. Delicious butter cakes and the icing was a winner. Highly recommended!
Prawn Briyani wasn't great. In fact, it was quite bad. I would recommend skipping this dish.
Mutton Igguru Fry was excellent. Spicy and is was so good. Must try!
Aloo Parata was not great. The filling was scanty. Could have been better.
Nellore Fish Curry was heavenly. A highly recommended dish!
Prawn Fry was nice. Lovely mix of masalas but the prawns itself felt a little old.

venue.name: Broga Recreational Fishing Park (武来岸石水烧鱼)

tip.text: Tried Tesco's Smoked Chicken Frankfurters and it was good. For RM 2 plus, this was a good bargain and worth the price paid. Highly recommended to try!
Giving this Tesco's Smoked Chicken Frankfurters a try. Cheap prices at RM 2 plus for 10. Will post the results soon.
Chicken Fried Rice was excellent. Came with lots of chicken and it was uniquely tasty. Highly recommended.
Mabo Tofu was nice. Slightly different to the Szehuan style and this had Japanese flavours to it. Loved it too. And the tofu was sliky soft.
Saba Shioyaki was excellent. Non greasy, crispy skin and extremely juicy meat. Loved it!
Chawan Mushi was one of the best that I have tasted. Hand crafted to perfection and literally melt in your mouth type. Comes with a variety of seafood in it. Must try!
Japanese Style Grilled Chicken Wings were very tasty. The marination was superb, crispy skin and juicy meat. Highly recommended.
Miso Soup was excellent. The blend of flavours were perfect and beautifully done.
Pickled Nutmeg with Sesame Seeds was excellent. Despite being served on the house, it had an instant refreshing effect. Good one!
Good variety for lunch but the food could have been better. Curries are watery too. If they spend a little more effort on the food, I'm sure they'll do well. Prices however are cheap. Decent service.
Pork Spring Rolls were heavenly. One of his best dishes. Highly recommended!
Steamed Fish with Chili Paste was delicious. A dish that I would recommend.
Claypot Beancurd was a little disappointing today. The ingredients were good but I felt it to be a little bland.
Petai Sambal is one that has been consistently good. Prices have gone up due to Petai's rising cost. Otherwise a good dish.
Pork Bacon it was for today and it was pretty good. Wasn't too greasy as well.
Fish Balls in clear soup was quite impressive. Not to be compared with Fish Castle Damansara, this was somewhat different and a taste of its own. A good one to have here.
Fish Ball Noodles was better than their Chili Pan Mee. Comes with soy sauce and pretty satisfying.
Chili Pan Mee was decent. Nowhere comparable to the both the outlets from Jalan Dewan Sultan Sulaiman or Madam Chiam, Cheras. Nevertheless still one that is at least three quarters there.
1/4 Barbecue Chicken was excellent. Loved the smokey marination and comes with a huge portion of fries. Highly recommended.
Fire Grilled Harvest Valley Chicken that is offered on their Lunch Sets was quite decent. A fusion between Malaysian and Western and surely value for money.
Suri's Nasi Lemak is the spicy one and can be a tad too spicy for those who can't handle it. But for spicy food lovers, you'd enjoy it for sure. Simple and delicious!
Thai Basil Chicken Rice was very good. The minced chicken was perfectly infused with the right spices and it was so authentic.
Hatyai Chicken Wings were excellent. Delicious marination, perfectly fried and so good. A must try here.
Thai Glass Noodles were good. Similar portions, similar tastes. Never did I feel that I was having this outside of Thailand. Authentic tastes!
Vegetarian Spicy Spring Rolls were good. Honestly, they weren't spicy but the crispy outer skin and juicy fillings were awesome. Highly recommended as well. And non greasy.
Thai Iced Tea was awesome! Very similar taste to the ones that we get in Thailand. Highly recommended.
Fish Cake was awesome. Lovely texture and it tasted so good. Must have!
Char Kui wasn't one to shout about as well. Just okay.

venue.name: Restaurant Hock Kee Bak Kut Teh & Seafood

tip.text: Tofu Pok wasn't good as well. It was stiff and dry, signs of it lacking freshness.

venue.name: Restaurant Hock Kee Bak Kut Teh & Seafood

tip.text: RM 7.00 for this small plate of mushrooms is just too much. Moreover, they weren't fresh either.

venue.name: Restaurant Hock Kee Bak Kut Teh & Seafood

tip.text: Bak Kut Teh was just okay. The tea wasn't up to my expectations and was a tad too sweet as well. I'd probably skip this and stick to the dry one the next time around.

venue.name: Restaurant Hock Kee Bak Kut Teh & Seafood

tip.text: Dry Bak Kut Teh was good, in fact very good. Comes with Okra and dried shrimps. Highly recommended.

venue.name: Restaurant Hock Kee Bak Kut Teh & Seafood

tip.text: Oyster Eggs were a shame. They had fried the Oysters first and topped it with fried eggs. Nowhere close to what it should have been. One to avoid!
Salted Egg Squid was another excellent dish. The thick batter of salted eggs and curry leaves were excellent. Highly recommended.
Kam Heong Clams were excellent. Very generous with the batter and it was heavenly. Highly recommended.
Grilled Stingray was a let down. The marination was bland and they relied too much of the chili paste to do the job. That too wasn't potent. I'd skip this the next time.
Sambal Petai was excellent. Love the fact that they stir fried it with Belacan and dried shrimps. A good one to try here.
Excellent hand made noodles. If you love mutton, try their noodles that comes with mutton curry. A beautiful blend of flavours that will take you to cloud 9. Highly recommended.
Their Mutton and Chicken Satay are must try items. Even if you skip the chicken, it's fine. He mutton is a must. Very different in taste, the meat is so tender and juicy and it was heavenly.
All that you see here is just for RM 45 . And that's including two Banana Leaf Meal sets. Totally worth it.
The food is definitely amazing. All cooked in earthen pots. Crab Curry is a must try here followed by mutton curry. The rest of the food items were good too. Highly recommended place for BLR lunch.
Vegetarian Spring Rolls were very nice. Non greasy and loved the crispy skin and juicy fillings. Decently priced too.
Vegetarian Mutton Curry with Rice was another good one. The curry was thick and full bodied. The mock mutton was up to the mark too. Highly recommended!
Vegetarian Bak Kut Teh is a must try here. The tea is so similar and they use up to 5 different types of mushrooms. Amazing it was.
Come for their lunch spread on weekdays as it's highly impressive. 30 plus dishes available daily and they are all so good. Mainly Malay Cuisine and spills over to Indonesian too. Must try.
Prawn Briyani was above average. Good portions for the price but the Masala Prawns could have been better and more in fact. I don't think I'd order this again unless they increase the Masala Prawns.
Thosai was excellent. One of the best plain Thosai's that I have tasted, on par with what you get in Tamil Nadu. Non greasy. Sambhar and Tomato Chutney were excellent. Coconut chutney was so so.
Egg Bhurji was good. Loved the mix of ingredients and spices. Recommended for sure!
Bru Coffee was excellent. One that you should not miss if you're a coffee lover.
Paal Appam was a disappointment. It was a little too dry and even the milk wasn't up to my expectations. I'd definitely pass the next time.
The best place for home cooked style food in Bandar Puteri. Mutton was awesome, Sardine Sambal was heavenly. In fact everything was so good including the Rasam. Cheap too!
Not the best that I have tasted but it was still good. Creamy crust and the filling was good.
Must have their Chili Paste with the Hokkien Mee. Tastes so good and way better than most Hokkien Mee places.
Fried Pork was awesome. Highly addictive.
Hokkien Mee is not the usual soggy version like Damansara Uptown. This is a little dry but I loved it. The texture of the noodles were great and the flavours were awesome. Good one to try.
Fried Chicken Wings were very good. This is one that I would recommend.
Food wasn't up to expectations. The Kulambu was diluted, Sambar was so so, vegetables were acceptable but nothing great and their Chicken Perattal was below average. Service however was good.
Salted Egg Squid was good as well. Generous with the Salted Egg batter and it was only RM 15. Very reasonable prices.
Kam Heong Clams were another dish that I would recommend. The gravy had diced dried shrimps and it was very good. RM 13 for this dish.
Sweet and sour prawns were good as well. Extra large prawns, 6 of them were used and these were as big as a adult make's palm. All for a mere RM 23. Must try!
Steamed Fish was very tasty and based on the current promotion price, it was only RM 19 for this dish. Highly recommended.
Mock Mutton Curry was above average as well. Decent but not as great as the one we get at Vege Good.

tip.text: They do sell a number of Murukkus and snacks. I tried their Ribbon Pakoda and Mixture. Both were good and reasonably priced at RM 13 per large jar.
Their complimentary sweet was quite unique and nice. Seemed like Kesari and tasted like oats. Good though.
Masala Tea was very good. Bold spices, less milk and more tea giving it a deep flavour.
Lacha Paratha is pretty much Roti Canai, but the non greasy version. Nice to have as a change from the usual rotis. But, it's basically Roti Canai.
Lime Pickles and Curd comes complementary with their Aloo Parata. These too items were excellent!
Aloo Parata was small and more expensive than other restaurants in Cyberjaya. The filling could have been better as well. However, the bread itself was soft and nice.
Chettinad Mutton was good. Medium spicy gravy and the cut size was perfect. Not too big, not too small. A good dish to try.
Malabar Prawns were above average. The prawns need to be crunchier and the flavours were also lacking.
Chettinad Crab Varuval was awesome. Cooked in a thick, mega spicy gravy along with banana blossoms. A must have for crab lovers. And it's only RM 27.
Salt Baked Chicken was nice. Tender, juicy and the blend of sweet soy sauce was nice. Braised Eggs were so so only.

tip.text: Fish Head Noodle was awesome! A must try for lovers of this dish.

venue.name: 幸运天美食館 Lucky Day Food Court

venue.name: 幸运天美食館 Lucky Day Food Court

tip.text: Their CKT is pretty good. Go for the special as it comes with all the add on's. Large is good to feed two medium eaters so choose your size wisely. Surely a good CKT to have.

tip.text: A very different kind of soup made with a variety of Indian spices. Thick and aromatic and can be eaten with bread or even rice. A good one to try in Kajang. Very different kind of texture.
Salted Egg Squid was extremely good. The squid was perfectly fried and the salted Egg batter was awesome.
Cheong Cheng style steamed fish was good. Thick gravy and loved it.
Kam Heong Clams is excellent. Highly recommended dish.
Kangkung Belacan is good. Fresh greens and generous shrimp paste.
The Cheese Cake was very good. Loved the springy texture and it melts in your mouth. Highly recommended.
